commit.message:
get_multi: Support an arbitrary collection of keys, not just a list

This is required for compatibility with Django.  Also fix an
IndexError if keys is empty.

Signed-off-by: Anders Kaseorg <andersk@mit.edu>

get_multi: Simplify away string decoding logic

By building the dictionary in two steps rather than one, we can avoid
the complicated test for whether to decode the keys to strings.  This
also reduces the running time from quadratic to linear.

Signed-off-by: Anders Kaseorg <andersk@mit.edu>

Use the length of key in bytes, not in characters

Signed-off-by: Anders Kaseorg <andersk@mit.edu>

Use b'' unconditionally

On Python 2, '' is the same as b'' anyway.

Signed-off-by: Anders Kaseorg <andersk@mit.edu>

Add missing files to docs.

Adding the mixin and the distributed modules to the docs.
